{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a small jug onto mixing bowl lid and weigh oil and lemon juice into it. Set aside.","Place Parmesan, garlic, pine nuts and pepitas into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b> or until finely chopped. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add spinach, coriander and salt and chop <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b>, mixing with aid of spatula.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then blend <b>1 min\/speed 3<b>, slowly adding reserved oil mixture through hole in mixing bowl lid. Serve as desired."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g extra virgin olive oil","40 g lemon juice","30 g Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces","1 garlic clove","30 g pine nuts","30 g pepitas","120 g fresh baby spinach leaves","40 g fresh coriander leaves","1 pinch sea salt"]}],"id":"r375228","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZYzomh8no1c\/XZaqTCI3vbI\/AAAAAAAAhbY\/LIEEhB95WXIkSng_k1Ajsimc7isI3BWegCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_UZ0y1xkbNPKp1p28.png","title":"Spinach and coriander pesto","publishedAt":"2019-05-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"28 g","fat":"105.1 g","uom":"per 1 Complete recipe","carbohydrates":"5.4 g","calories":"4574.2 kJ \/ 1089.1 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small jug","hintsAndTricks":["This pesto can also be served to young children. Try starting with a very small serve - perhaps mixed with a favourite food - to help them accept the flavour.","Serve on top of soup such as pumpkin, as a dip, spread on cheese toasties or serve with steak or lamb cutlets."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","10m","1"]}